                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12607: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-31T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 31, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 31—11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>943. Legation’s 941, December 30, 10 p.m. Following has been sent to Peck at
                    Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 81, 1 p.m. Your December 30, noon, has been repeated to the
                            Consuls at Amoy and Foochow. You may so inform the Foreign Office, but
                            should state that the advice contained in its note cannot be regarded as
                            in any way absolving the Chinese Government from full responsibility for
                            the safety of Americans and American property not only at Kulangsu and
                            Nantai Island but in all of Fukien Province.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
